hopobject.body: I've just graduated medical world solutions TEAM MVP: Robinson Cano had another MVP-caliber season both offensively and defensively, finishing the season over .300 (.314) for the seventh time -- with 27 homers and 107 RBIs -- despite a lineup without several regulars for much of the year. But now Cano, who left agent Scott Boras to retain Jay-Z's new agency as representation, expects to be compensated as one of the game's premier stars. "Who knows what's going to happen," Cano said on Sept. 25. "Nobody said I'm leaving, nobody said that I'm staying. I haven't decided anything yet. Let's see what happens after the World Series. But don't get me wrong. I love this team."
